//
// Release build configuration.
//
// The relay onion address is NEVER published or committed. It is injected from
// the build environment at build time so the relay hidden service stays out of
// the source tree.
//
// Deliberately NOT set here as "RELAY_ONION_ADDRESS = $(RELAY_ONION_ADDRESS)" —
// that line was self-referential (a build setting defined in terms of itself,
// with no other source to resolve against) and evaluated to empty/unresolved
// regardless of the environment. Xcode already exposes a process environment
// variable as a build setting of the same name when no xcconfig/project setting
// shadows it, so the correct way to inject the value is to export it in the
// environment that invokes the build, e.g.:
//
//   RELAY_ONION_ADDRESS=<relay>.onion xcodebuild -project Sublemonable.xcodeproj \
//     -scheme Sublemonable -configuration Release archive ...
//
// Support/Info.plist reads it via a RELAY_ONION_ADDRESS key set to
// "$(RELAY_ONION_ADDRESS)", substituted from that build setting at build time;
// Swift reads the resulting value via RelayConfig.onionAddress
// (Sources/Networking/RelayConfig.swift), which wraps
// Bundle.main.infoDictionary["RELAY_ONION_ADDRESS"]. Empty when unset.
